public class LongLinkedListStore extends PrimitiveListStore
Stores linked lists of long values in a space efficient way.

The add(int, long) method takes a list identifier and adds the given value to the head of the list, returning an identifier to the new list. To start a new list, pass NEW_LIST as the list identifier. To retrieve the list as an LongIterator, call list(int) with the list identifier.

Author:
jonathanl (shibo)
